
QUIZIT react vite .NET project 


Directory Structure

The .NET backend is located in the 'api' folder.
The React frontend is located in the 'quizitFront' folder.

Running the Project

if you are running on vs code use two terminals, one for the front-end and one for the backend. 

To run the backend, navigate to the 'api' folder and use the command:

dotnet build
dotnet run
This will start the backend on localhost:5241.

To run the frontend, navigate to the '' folder and use the command:

npm run dev

This will start the frontend on localhost:5173.

If the front-end is not running try this command: 
npm install

Steps to test the backend functionality:

1. Open a terminal.

2. Navigate to the API folder using cd api.

3. Run dotnet build.

4. Start the application with dotnet run.

5. Open the localhost link in your browser and append /swagger to the URL.

6. You can now test the endpoints that donâ€™t require owner authorization.

7. To test all endpoints, register a new user.

8. Log in, you will receive a token. Paste this token into the Authorize button to gain access to protected endpoints.

9. You can now test all functions.
